data.text:
Susan J. Duffrin, 72, of La Crosse, Wis., died Sunday, April 7, 2019, in Benedictine Manor, La Crosse, Wis.,

She was born in La Crosse, Wis., on Oct. 11, 1946, to Lewis and Beverley (Welch) Jones. She married Robert G. Duffrin on March 30, 1970 in St. James the Less Catholic Church, La Crosse, Wis.

She is survived by her husband, Robert G Duffrin of La Crosse, Wis., two daughters; Tammy (Calvin) Flick of Eau Claire, Wis., and Tracy Duffrin of Duluth, Minn., three sons; Broeck Duffrin of La Crosse, Wis., Kevin Duffrin of Tomah, Wis., and Bradley (Jess) Duffrin of De Forest, Wis., two grandchildren Christian and Adranna Duffrin, one sister; Judy (Francis) Anderson of Northfield, Minn., and one brother Ralph (Patricia Burton) Jones of Ft. Worth, Texas.

She was preceded in death by her parents.

A funeral Mass will be held at 11:00 AM Thursday, April 11, 2019, in St. James the Less Catholic Church, 1032 Caledonia St., La Crosse, Wis. Rev. James Altman will officiate with burial to be held in the French Island Cemetery, La Crosse, Wis. Family and friends may visit from 10:00 AM until the time of Mass in the Church on Thursday.
